{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SuWuzhDxmor78YuCt152vF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n     6→- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n     7→- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n     8→- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n     9→\n    10→## Token Report\n    11→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    12→- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n    13→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    14→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n    15→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e02dc85a-4a74-462d-837f-c292e168b489","uuid":"e674e247-ebcf-4cf5-9e6f-c1e32255eb83","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:44:59.482Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n","numLines":15,"startLine":1,"totalLines":15}}}
