{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a67ed54b2a99d4f0b","tool_use_id":"toolu_01N75byRJieFL4ujBqrddJvw","description":"Session retrospective","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Run a session retrospective for the codeharness sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis.\n\nThis was a NO-OP session (session 33). All 74 stories were already done. The only work was fixing recurring state corruption where Ralph's stale in-memory state keeps reverting stories 16-5 through 16-8 from `done` to `review`. This is the 17th time this has been fixed.\n\nKey context:\n- All 17 epics (0-16) are done, all 74 stories are done\n- The Ralph process (PID unknown, started morning of 2026-03-27) has stale in-memory state\n- The `registerStory` guard prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't fix ralph's cached state\n- Every new session Ralph spawns hits the same issue: reads stale ralph state, finds stories at `review`, no work to do except re-fix\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. Session summary — no-op, state fix only\n2. Issues analysis — the ralph state corruption is the ONLY issue, categorize it\n3. Cost analysis — from the cost report\n4. What went well — sprint is done\n5. What went wrong — ralph state corruption recurring\n6. Lessons learned — need to fix ralph's state management\n7. Action items — fix ralph to re-read from disk or restart it\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md. If a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","uuid":"15a76